text.tspan: MDG5.B: Share of pregnant women receiving adequate antenatal care,
Millennium Development Goal (MDG) 5.B was the share of pregnant women in developing regions receiving adequate
antenatal care (which is defined as at least 4 antenatal visits). The target was to achieve universal antenatal care for pregnant
women by 2015. This target was not achieved.
